definitions.definition: A small, fleshy excrescence that is a normal part of an animal's anatomy .
Clipping of lacrimal caruncle : the red prominence at the inner corner of the eye .
A colored waxy or oily outgrowth near the micropyle of some seeds , attractive to ants which aid the seed's dispersal .

main_definition: ( anatomy , zootomy ) A small, fleshy excrescence that is a normal part of an animal's anatomy .
